This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on compressing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, the paper mentions the VGG-16 model which is a popular CNN architecture for image classification. 

The paper also involves optimization techniques and proposes a novel filter selection criteria, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Furthermore, the paper involves reducing computational cost and inference time, which could also place it in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves developing techniques to reduce overfitting, which could also place it in the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
